                <note rend="inline" type="source">853.51/315: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Portugal</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dearing</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lisbon</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-01-21T12:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 21, 1926—noon</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received January 22—9:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5. My No. 4, January 19. I have just received note dated January 19 from Foreign
                    Office informing me that redemption of the bonds and payment of arrears of
                    interest tobacco loan will be made in pounds sterling so that American citizens
                    will receive same treatment that was accorded British subjects. Probably this is
                    note promised me by Dr. Teixeira. The Department will observe that there is no
                    direct statement where Americans will be paid, although this may be London, and
                    that by failing to state a place, date, and period for making payment, treatment
                    equivalent to that accorded British holders of bonds is by no means accorded to
                    Americans.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dearing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
